## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Install (prefer uv)
uv sync --extra dev

# 2. Set credentials (copy and edit)
cp .env.example .env

# 3. Verify the graph compiles
uv run pytest tests/unit -q

# 4. Run
uv run python -m {{ package_name }}
```

## Changing deployment target

`src/{{ package_name }}/deploy.py` picks the adapter. Swap one import line
to migrate without touching graph.py or specialists.py:

```python
# Direct (local / self-hosted LangGraph):
from langgraph_forge.deploy.direct import DirectAdapter as Adapter

# AWS Bedrock AgentCore Runtime:
# from langgraph_forge.deploy.bedrock import BedrockAgentCoreAdapter as Adapter

# GCP Vertex Agent Engine:
# from langgraph_forge.deploy.vertex import VertexAgentEngineAdapter as Adapter

# Azure AI Agent Service:
# from langgraph_forge.deploy.azure import AzureAIAgentAdapter as Adapter
```
